(254, 'Thorsten Leissner', '00497032917643', 'thors111@t-online.de', 'Herrenberg', 'DE', 'info', 'our Childrenwish', '<p>Dear Mrs.<a href=\"http://cduh.com.ph/ourdoctors/profile/73\">Dr.Milagros Chan</a>,</p><p>My lifepartner April Delacruz is now in your department and waiting.I want,that you examinate her by&nbsp;ultrasound and a vaginal examination with bacterial and virological investigation.I want to know , if she can easily get children.My problem is clear ,since my last examination here in Germany.The result is following:</p><p>Spermiogramm(WHO-criteria) from the 4th of December 2014</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Birthday 18th February 1966</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Examination:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>liquefaction time:35 min</p><p>Volumen:2 ml</p><p>PH- pix under 7.2</p><p>sperm concentration :8 Millions/ml</p><p>total amount of sperms 16 Millions</p><p>mobility:PR(progressiv)38%</p><p>total mobility 38%</p><p>Morphologie:15%</p><p>Vitality:70%</p><p>no bacteria detected</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Result:Oligozoospermy with tendency to asthenozoospermy<br /><br />Please,give us suggestions in which kind you can support us to become the next time parents and pls.give April Delacruz&nbsp;a written diagnose(in english)from the examination from todsay.</p><p>Thank you for your support.</p><p>Thorsten Leissner</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '12/17/2014 12:02:15 pm', 'read', 'Archive'),
