(325, 'Samuel Buettner', '00491732818415', 'samuel_buettner@yahoo.de', 'Tuebingen - Southern Germany', 'DE', 'er', 'Medical Visitation University of Tuebingen, Southern Germany', '<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p><p>as a medical student in the 9th term of study (4,5 years) at the University of T&uuml;bingen in Southern Germany I have always been interested to become acquainted to medical care in other countries, especially in the Philippines.&nbsp;</p><p>Therefore I am searching for a hospital that might give foreign students a chance of a &quot;Medical Visitation&quot;.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>So the reason why I`m writing to you is the question whether there is a chance of &nbsp;&ldquo;Medical Visitation&rdquo; at your Hospital. &nbsp;Furthermore it would be of my interest to spend four weeks visiting your emergency room in summer, exactly August or September.</strong></p><p>I would be very happy to hear from you and thanks a lot for your help!</p><p>Lots of greetings,</p><p>Samuel Buettner</p><p><strong>P.S.: Description of what is meant by &quot;Medical Visitation&quot;</strong></p><p>&ldquo;Medical Visitation&rdquo; of a Hospital is the German equivalent of &quot;Famulatur&quot;<br /><br />Please allow me to introduce you to the German &quot;Famulatur&quot;. It has no counterpart in the AngloSaxon medical system. It is not equivalent to what is known as a clerkship or an elective in your medical educational system.</p><p>One &quot;Famulatur&quot; consists of a minimal four-week visitation by a German medical student to a hospital with the purpose of acquainting her or him with the daily routine of a hospital. It is performed by each student during the clinical years of study (which are the 3rd to 5th years of a 6 year program). The specific aim of this visitation is to give the ongoing medical student insight into the daily duties of the physician in a hospital. The participation of the visiting student in this routine may consist of including her/him in medical history taking, observing physical examinations, and participating in the discussion of the case histories of the patients on a ward. Listening-in on the staff discussion of patients&#39; x-rays, CTs and other clinical findings and the resulting patient management will help to emphasize to the students the essentials and pertinent aspects of patient care and will help in orienting their further medical studies.</p>', '02/10/2015 06:04:21 am', 'read', 'Archive'),
(326, 'Samuel Buettner', '00491732818415', 'samuel_buettner@yahoo.de', 'Tuebingen - Southern Germany', 'DE', 'hr', 'Medical Visitation University of Tuebingen, Southern Germany', '<p>Dear Sir or Madam,</p><p>as a medical student in the 9th term of study (4,5 years) at the University of T&uuml;bingen in Southern Germany I have always been interested to become acquainted to medical care in other countries, especially in the Philippines.&nbsp;</p><p>Therefore I am searching for a hospital that might give foreign students a chance of a &quot;Medical Visitation&quot;.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>So the reason why I`m writing to you is the question whether there is a chance of &nbsp;&ldquo;Medical Visitation&rdquo; at your Hospital. &nbsp;Furthermore it would be of my interest to spend four weeks visiting your emergency room in summer, exactly August or September.</strong></p><p>I would be very happy to hear from you and thanks a lot for your help!</p><p>Lots of greetings,</p><p>Samuel Buettner</p><p><strong>P.S.: Description of what is meant by &quot;Medical Visitation&quot;</strong></p><p>&ldquo;Medical Visitation&rdquo; of a Hospital is the German equivalent of &quot;Famulatur&quot;<br /><br />Please allow me to introduce you to the German &quot;Famulatur&quot;. It has no counterpart in the AngloSaxon medical system. It is not equivalent to what is known as a clerkship or an elective in your medical educational system.</p><p>One &quot;Famulatur&quot; consists of a minimal four-week visitation by a German medical student to a hospital with the purpose of acquainting her or him with the daily routine of a hospital. It is performed by each student during the clinical years of study (which are the 3rd to 5th years of a 6 year program). The specific aim of this visitation is to give the ongoing medical student insight into the daily duties of the physician in a hospital. The participation of the visiting student in this routine may consist of including her/him in medical history taking, observing physical examinations, and participating in the discussion of the case histories of the patients on a ward. Listening-in on the staff discussion of patients&#39; x-rays, CTs and other clinical findings and the resulting patient management will help to emphasize to the students the essentials and pertinent aspects of patient care and will help in orienting their further medical studies.</p>', '02/10/2015 06:05:49 am', 'read', 'Archive'),
