(549, 'Rebecca Smith', '00447872053419', 'rxs189@bham.ac.uk', 'Birmingham', 'GB', 'Admin', 'Medical Elective', '<p>Dear Sir/Madam,&nbsp;</p><p>I am a fourth year medical student at the University of Birmingham, UK. I am considering doing a four week&nbsp;medical elective in the Philippines in May 2016.&nbsp;My interests are in infectious/tropical diseases, surgery, obs and gyne, cardiology and neurology.&nbsp;I have recently completed an intercalated degree in international health for which I spent three months in India doing research on the use of mHealth in cardiovascular disease management; thus I also have an interest in mHealth research in the developing world.&nbsp;Has your hospital accommodated overseas students on medical elective before? Please do let me know if there is anyone in particular I can get in contact with or any other information concerning medical electives at your hospital.&nbsp;</p><p>Many thanks,</p><p>Rebecca Smith</p>', '05/28/2015 12:14:57 am', 'read', 'Done'),
