(715, 'Goring Borromeo', '0932-1677-998', 'gingdonayre@hotmail.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'hr', 'Feedback about the Secretary of Dr. Nelson Cantillas at clinic room # 305', '<p>Good Day,</p><p>I wish to give a feedback on the secretary of Dr.Karen Cantillas at the Medical Arts Building room 305 for what i have encountered today.&nbsp;</p><p>Earlier today, August 13, 2015. I went to the clinic to schedule an appointment for my Mother with Dr. Karen Batoctoy which was referred to us by our family - cardiologist, Dr. Robert Cantoy. It was around 11am when i reached the clinic. Upon opening the clinics door, i met the secretary at her desk on her cellphone talking to someone, she paused when i sheepishly asked if Dr. Karen Batoctoy will be in today, she responded saying, her secretary is not around yet and advised met to just come back after 12, cause the secretary wont normally be in until about past 12 noon, i was about to ask a follow up question if it&#39;s ok to wait for her instead cause upon checking my phone the time was already at 11:40am &nbsp;and it should not be long for the secretary to arrive - however, i did not have a chance to speak up cause she already gestured her hand for me to close the door and go away while she looked away and went back to her conversation on the phone saying &quot;Unya Ma&quot;(sounded to me she was talking with her Mom)<br />&nbsp;<br />With that, i decided to just wait outside the clinic and sat down on one of those chairs at the hallway. I was a bit taken aback and i guess it was more of the gesture - how she &quot;shooed&quot; me away like a fly.&nbsp;</p><p>On my Mp3 listening to my audio book while scanning pics of my 8 month old baby on my cellphone, i thought i can just wait for few minutes until the secretary would arrive,get a schedule for Mom then head home to rest(I work night shift). It was when i realized my earpiece&#39;s audio was really not at its best and I end up having to press the tiny button- attached on the wire in order for the audio to sound louder or be audible for that matter. I dont know why its design that way, but its annoying that i have to press the tiny thing on the wire to get the full audio otherwise the music or voice or whatever i am listening to will never be audible.&nbsp;</p><p>It was when i thought, maybe i can go ahead and ask the secretary for a cellophane tape, maybe i can wrap that around this tiny button thing to ensure a full audio, that way i can sit there longer and comfortably while waiting for Dr. Batoctoy&#39;s secretary.&nbsp;</p><p>I stood up and opened the door, &quot;Ma&#39;am excuse me&quot;, she did not budge. Never looked at my direction. Despite i am just 45 degree angle from her direction. She was staring at the glass wall next to the glass door where i was standing, still on her phone while at her desk. I asked again, &quot;uhm, excuse Ma&#39;am&#39;. To no avail, i close the door and just stood there for 3 to 5 seconds outside the clinic. I decided to open the door again, &quot;Sorry, Ma&#39;am&quot;...She interrupted in an angry tone, &quot;Unsa man Mam?! Wala pa iyang secretary!, ingun ko 12 pa mo abot&quot;. Appaled, I answered, &quot;Sorry, naa unta ko pangutana:, then she said, &quot;Dili ko maka tubag nimo, diba ingun ko dili ako ang Secretary ni Dr. Batoctoy, dili ko maka tubag kung unsa imong pangutana!&quot; She was literally yelling. I, in a slow voice, maybe due to disbelief of what i am seeing and hearring, said &quot;Kahibalo na diay ka unsa akong pangutana Mam? wala paman ko naka ask nimo unsa about akong i pangutana?&quot; - she interrupted, &quot;ingun ko dili ko maka tubag nimo bisan unsa pa na imong pangutana kay dili ko secretary niya, bisan unsa pa na imong pangutana dinha, dili gyud ko maka tubag nimo kay dili ciya ang nagpa sweldo nko!&quot; Her eyes were fierce and sounded more angry this time, she would not even let me finished.&nbsp;</p><p>Shaken and appaled, In a slow fainted voices, &quot;ingun ani ka mo treat sa mga taw nga imong ka istorya ngari? Kabalo ka ang mga taw imong ka deal diri, kay naay mga sakit, tapos ingun ana ka mo treat nila?&quot; she responded in the same yelling, &quot;bundak, isug&quot; look, &quot;wala koy labot sa mga pasyente sa uban Doctor!Akong trabaho kay ang mga pasyente ra sa akong Doctor, wala nkoy mahimo sa akong tingug! inguna ani na gyud ni cia!. So, I said, &quot;Nganu suko man kaayu ka? Medyu tense lagi ka Mam?&quot;, hoping to diffuse her, then she said, &quot;ingun ani &nbsp;na gyud ko,wala na kay labot ana, ganiha raman gud ka daghan pangutana gud! ganiha raman ka sige ug samok, padung ko manid-udto&quot;.&nbsp;</p><p>I thought to myself, this is not worth it, i am not going to give in to her nasty remarks and insult. I asked her for the last time, &quot;Kinsa imong doctor gi silbihan? She answered, Dr. Cantillas. So i said, &quot;Aw,cge. Sorry kaayu Ma&#39;am naka disturbo ko nimo Ma&#39;am and intentionally said that with sarcasm.&nbsp;</p><p>Shaken, I took my seat and pondered, how could I be treated this way? I am not even stressed at work, I was not in a bad mood not exuding any negative aura when approaching her at the onset. It was a relaxing easy breezy day after work for me until now. I could not fathom how someone could be so hurtful, insensitive, way way too verbally abusive and maligning to patients. Do they not go through a training how to at least provide a satisfactory customer service? or just anything basic about work etiquette?</p><p>I said to myself, i am not going to be affected, but &nbsp;I am going to give feedback to Dr. Cantillas herself in time. Suddenly, it occured to me, that my Mother would be coming here in this clinic, possibly getting this experience. I am not going to allow that. My Mom has a liver mass seen at her ultrasound result, and she has gone through a lot of medical ordeals for the past 3 years, she does not deserved to be treated this way.</p><p>I opted to stand up and took a pic of the glass wall to get the full name of the Doctor and realized my Mother&#39;s one time Doctor, Mitzi Chua is also here! I felt somehow gladness that she is also here cause i dont like her other clinic at Velez Hospital. It&#39;s refreshing to know we can just come here should the need arise in the future.</p><p>After taking 2 shots from my phone, I sat down again, put my shades on, realizing i was a bit teary eyed, maybe with the whole experience with the secretary. Still shaken a bit but i went on listening to my audio book while scanning the pics of my baby and at the same time still pressing that tiny button of the earpiece to hear my audio well. She suddeny, came out of the clinic, locking the door with her key and remarked, &quot;tarunga gyud ug post sa FB ha!&quot;.&nbsp;</p><p>I did not show any sign that i heard her with that - i don&#39;t even know how to describe anymore that behavior. I wanted to pretend unaffected and that I did not hear her at all. She left. Minutes later, returned and follewed by a new lady, i hurriedly took off my shades asking &quot;ikaw ang Secretary ni Dr. Batoctoy?&quot; she nodeed then i followed her inside the clinic. We exchanged greetings and i wrote my Mother&#39;s name on the sheet of small paper so she can write it somewhere else. She, Lani, the Secretary of Dr. Batoctoy then advised me to have ask my Mother to come to the clinic immediately since the doctor is already heading her way. I told her, i am going home and I will let her know.&nbsp;</p><p>The other secretary whom i had that awful experience with, was just there at the back ground, attending to whatever she was doing, i never gave a look to bother whatever she was doing. I wanted to just completely ignore her presence.&nbsp;</p><p>I left the clinic. Appaled. In disbelief with the whole experience. I apologize for this letany-like narration of what had happened.&nbsp;</p><p>I do not believe, I or anyone for that matter, deserved to be treated that way. At all. Bar non. I cannot fathom, what right mind would even treat someone that way. I could be the ill patient who could not be in a good condition or shape to experience the whole ordeal or very disturbing &nbsp;bahavior. I felt maligned, disrespected, slandered, shamed and attacked verbally by behavior. When the least expected treatment i could get from someone in the healthcare environment is this. I wanted to share this experience to the right authority and i really am hoping for your compassion and understanding that I, beyond words really felt abused verbally. I do not know what your parameters are in this behavior or what the hospital or the doctor concerned could ever do for cases like this. &nbsp;I do not want to go public on FB,cause i think it&#39;s really a cheap way to get heard. I still believe in proper channeling when providing feedback. I really hope you will prove me right with my faith. Please, I beg you- train your secretaries proper etiquette, proper behavior, customer service, public service or even simple manners.&nbsp;</p><p>Feel free to reach out to me:</p><p>Dumbfounded<br />Goring D. Borromeo<br />0932-1677-998</p><p><br />&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '08/14/2015 12:51:20 am', 'read', 'Pending'),
