(729, 'Mayen Edge', '09285215586', 'mayen.edge@me.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'info', 'Poor service (VIP room) - Disappointing Check-in', '<p>We decided to be in the VIP room as it said to have the best amenities but we&#39;re so disappointed. I came personally to the Admission dept./Information to get the room (501) reserved on Saturday (August 15, 2015)&nbsp;to be ready for&nbsp;today,Monday at 9am (August 1, 2015). I asked to make sure the room is ready at 9am and they said it wouldn&#39;t be a problem because nobody is staying in the VIP room.&nbsp;</p><p>We arrived past 12pm as my patient&nbsp;(my husband) had a hard tim getting ready this morning. We asked to check in and and I was quite sure the room is ready since it was supposed to be 9am. We&#39;ve been asked to wait for the concierge to pick us up to take us to our room.&nbsp;I asked again and they&nbsp;said just to wait and he was coming down. Another 10 minutes had past. My patient&nbsp;wears a face mask to protect himself. He&#39;s not supposed to be in crowded area as his immune system is still weak from all the Chemotherapy and Radiation he had. He felt so uncomfortable with his face mask as it was getting crowded in there and it was getting hot. I asked the counter again as I started to realize that the room might not ready but we really need to get out of there as it was getting crowded and I wanted to take my patient away from the crowd. Ironically they told me that the room was in fact ready but since we arrived late they locked the room again and they were looking for somebody who has the key. Unbelievable!</p><p>Another 5 minutes had past, total of 20 minutes of waiting of the supposedly &quot;VIP Express Check-in&quot;. I finally did complain with frustration on how ridiculous the service is and it was no longer acceptable if we have to wait longer. That was the only time they heard me. somebody from concierge came to take us to the room and&nbsp;to my surprise about 3 people&nbsp;were making the bed as fast as they could.&nbsp;They said that they were only got instruction to make the room and wished that they know earlier so they can make the room before our arrival. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Why lying to us? Especially for those who are willing to pay the highest room rate with the expectation that it comes with the best service. If I didn&#39;t complain they might have us waited longer till the room is finally ready with all the lies that it was ready,&nbsp;with the&nbsp;unbelivable and unacceptable alibi that they only wait somebody who got the key.</p><p>Very disappointing and unacceptable especialy for the discomfort of&nbsp;my patient who has shortness of breath with face mask on to protect himself from another illness he can get from the crowd.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>(Update: as of August 17, 2015 at 8:18pm)&nbsp;</p><p>1. Dinner is not yet served.</p><p>2. No rugs in the kitchen area and bathroom.</p><p>3. Both phones aren&#39;t working.</p><p>The room is not completely ready.</p>', '08/17/2015 08:46:32 pm', 'unread', 'Pending'),
