(770, 'Derik Kyle M. Tabunar', '0915-149-1986', 'dkmt.habitat@gmail.com', 'Manila, NCR', 'PH', 'Admin', 'Habitat for Humanity Partnership', '<p>Dear Engr. Oscar Tuason,</p><p>I am Derik Tabunar from Habitat for Humanity Philippines. As you may know, we are an International Non-Profit and Non-Government Organisation&nbsp;committed to provide quality, decent homes to the less privileged in our society, and rehabilitating communities devastated by natural disasters. We are currently determined to help our fellow Filipinos in the Visayas area, primarily&nbsp;those affected by the Bohol earthquake and Yolanda typhoon by providing decent&nbsp;housing and safe community to the&nbsp;unfortunate families&nbsp;still residing in relocation sites.&nbsp;We were hoping to develop&nbsp;a&nbsp;partnership with Cebu Doctor&#39;s and its affiliate hospitals, given its honorable philanthropic stand on helping the poverty stricken families through its medical missions, to help us in our Dream Builder and Re-Build campaign&nbsp;by allowing us to encourage its doctors and employees to donate to our cause.&nbsp;We plan to do so by setting up a donor sign up&nbsp;booth at your allowed area in Cebu Doctor&#39;s at any date on October 5-9, 2015. We are positive that through this action, we can, together with Cebu Doctor&#39;s and its affiliate hospitals, help give families a clean slate to start with through a decent home. With all humility and greatfulness, we thank you for your time in considering this avenue to help those in need&nbsp;to which we&nbsp;are greatly looking forward to hear from your organisation soon.&nbsp;</p><p>Sincerely,</p><p>Derik Kyle M. Tabunar</p><p>Account Executive</p><p>0915-149-1986/dkmt.habitat@gmail.com</p><p>http://www.habitat.org.ph</p>', '09/02/2015 01:01:09 pm', 'read', 'Pending'),
