(805, 'Leonard Kulleseid', '017756571312', 'unfetered1@yahoo.com', 'Prescott Valley', 'US', 'info', 'Cataract Surgery', '<p>I am leaving US Oct 21, will have cataract surgery for both eyes prior, first on September 30, the other 2 weeks later, which leaves me only one week, between surgery and flight time.</p><p>I need to know if follow-up can be done there, as I have few options, that would not be very costly.</p><p>Am on the phone daily with VA and TriWest. &nbsp;The initial request for approval from VA was mid April, and finally being approved, my doctor wants me to stay until January 1, I am not willing to delay my coming any longer, not to mention the costs of changing itinerary, and/or, filing claim on my flight insurance which may or may not be approved.</p><p>The airline will not penalize me for delay, depending on how long the delay is, so not sure there either.</p><p>I have a letter from VA/TriWest that lists the services needed, including diagnostic and procedure codes.</p><p>My question is, post surgery, what can you provide post-op as to costs I would incur, and of course, when it would be safe to do so.</p><p>Any advice or recommendations would be greatly appreciated, to have all prodedures done there is cost prohibitive, yet certain if simple follow-up, I can afford that.</p><p>If you could provide an email address to send this to, would be more than happy to provide a .pdf document attachment as to the what the VA has authorized, though I know it is my responsibility to pay.</p><p>Salamat...</p><p>Leonard Kulleseid</p>', '09/15/2015 07:40:06 am', 'read', 'Done'),
