(1017, 'Graeme Campbell ', '447714580889', 'Graeme_c@live.com', 'London', 'GB', 'info', 'Chemo in Philippines', '<p>Hello - I hope you can help me.</p><p>I am a 35 year old British male who was diagnosed with stage 3 metastatic bowel cancer in May 2013. Since then I have had surgery, radiotherapy and chemotherapy to remove the&nbsp;primary tumour and metastases but currently present signs in my lung and recurrence in the original site (the anastamosis I think is the word).</p><p>After 3 years of constant treatment I needed a break and am planning to spend the next few months relaxing in the Philippines, which gave me a thought - would it be possible to access chemotherapy treatment there with you? I realise this would come at a cost as I&#39;m a foreigner, so could you please let me know if this might be possible and give me some idea of what a course of 12 rounds of Folifiri (with or&nbsp;without Aflibercept)&nbsp;might cost?</p><p>If you could please&nbsp;come back to me via email it would be much appreciated as I&#39;m currently in Australia and am not available on the above number - FYI I arrive in Cebu on 18 January.</p><p>Thank you so much</p><p>Kind regards&nbsp;</p><p>Graeme</p>', '01/11/2016 05:40:46 am', 'read', 'Pending'),
(1018, 'Sohaida Dulguime', '09778052904', 'sohaida_dimapundug@yahoo.com.ph', 'Surigao city', 'PH', 'info', 'biopsy procedure and Dr Don Edward Rosello', '<p>Hi Good Day!</p><p>My mother had undergone 2 ERCP procedures by Dr Rosello. Unfortunately she had been suffering severe pain at abdomen and chest. We wish to have the wire (used in Ercp) be removed already and conduct biopsy to test if she has cancer.</p><p>I&#39;d like to talk to DR ROSELLO as I cannot get through the landline number posted to the website.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I also would like to know if Dr Rosello can perform biopsy or other medical person will do it. How much is the biopsy?</p>', '01/11/2016 10:41:18 am', 'read', 'Pending'),
