(1253, 'Matthew Walke', '09274881400', 'matthew_walke@hotmail.co.uk', 'cebu', 'PH', 'Admin', 'Ongoing digestive/stomach problem', '<p>I have been having stomach problems after I eat for the last 4 weeks. I have been to the doctors and had my stool checked for parasites, the result showed to be clear. I usually eat quite cleanly and consume 4 or 5 meals a day in accordance with training in the gym. My weight has dropped from 100kg to 96kg. I have been eating less since having this problem since I am worried which might explain the weight loss!</p><p>My symptoms after eating are belching followed by stomach ache and then dioreah. This doesnt happen with every meal usually towards the end of the day, but it is happening nearly every day. I also have been suffering with stress and mild anxiety and have read that this could be linked to my symptoms. If i dont have dioreah then its usually constipation.</p><p>I am a British male aged 37 and have been working in Cebu for 5 months, I have never previously had stomach issues like this.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '05/02/2016 09:32:48 pm', 'read', 'Pending'),
