(1266, 'Jerry TW Chow', '60163388882', 'pjerrychow@gmail.com', 'Kuala Lumpur', 'MY', 'Admin', 'Request For Assistance', '<p>Date:&nbsp;9th May 2016</p><p>To: <strong>Hospital Administrator, </strong><em><strong>Oscar A. Tuason</strong>,&nbsp;</em></p><p>Re: <strong>Letter of Urgent Request,</strong></p><p>Warm greetings! This is with regards to my personal friend, Jane Guiral, who recently worked at the Operating Room at CDUH. She was sent for an OTJ training at Manila hospital (6th-8th) and scheduled for confirmation of her status as a nurse with CDUH. She was required to undergo a medical examination and submit the medical report back to the management office. She took the medical exam at the clinic at Manila but the results of the medical test were delayed. She had to return back to Cebu City on Sunday night. As the test result was not ready, she is not able to submit the medical report to the management. Consequently, she cannot report for work as well as receive her salary. The clinic has called Jane and informed her that there are no issues with her health.She is in a predicament as she does not have the financial means for the mailing fees for the medical report to be sent to the management office and cannot start work. As such I write to your good self&nbsp;for a special assistance to Jane Guiral in terms of an advance to enable her to have the financial means for the medical report to be sent to the management office to fulfill the hospital requirement so that she could start work.I write this letter of urgent appeal for your kind consideration to help Jane Guiral to solve this problem so that she can start work and receive her salary later on. She looked forward to going to start work. At the same time, she needed financial assistance.</p><p>Thank you in advance for your consideration and action.</p><p>Yours&nbsp;sincerely,</p><p>Thank you,</p><p>Jerry TW Chow</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '05/09/2016 11:40:23 pm', 'unread', 'Pending'),
