(1418, 'Roselyn', '09054623296', 'ra129@cairn.edu', 'Davao City', 'PH', 'hr', 'Complain for Macon Doctor\'s ER Nurse Staff', '<p>Hi Cebu Doctor&#39;s HR department,</p><p>I understad that you are NOT Mactan Doctor&#39;s but I am aware that you are a group of companies. My Mom had a running fever and we happened to be staying at Waterfront Mactan. The hotel voluntered to send my Mom to the hospital to be sure of what&#39;s really going on with her. So off we went. This happened on July 10 around 8PM. The hospital&#39;s service wasn&#39;t a great one but good&nbsp;enough to help us feel at ease to know what&#39;s wrong with my Mom&#39;s physical concerns. They asked us to run a couple of lab tests and asked to come back after an hour. We failed to go back after an hour but instead around 5:30AM the following day. The results were ready and available but unfortunately they asked us to wait for the doctor to come who was somewhere in the building for something. They staff told us he might be taking his shower. I expressed my concern that I need to head back to the hotel before 6AM to arrange a flight back to Davao around 10AM in order to receive more medical help for my Mom. The&nbsp;staff who were around&nbsp;said the results looked fine but they were just a bit unsure of the &quot;Blood 3+&quot; item.&nbsp;It was already shortly after 6AM so I begged if they could help us read the results. They tried to call the doctor again but to no avail. I insisted that I needed to leave soon because I still need to arrange our Davao flight. One of the staff said I can go and the result is just fine. I was surprised. Why did they ask&nbsp;me to wait when they could read the results themselves. Anyways, I left... At around 10AM I called back the hospital with the hope to speak with any of the doctors to double check about the results before we fly back to Davao. I was able to speak with Nurse Disney Salarda who spoke and answered my questions&nbsp;arrogantly.&nbsp;I admit I was a bit in a rush and might have sounded so &quot;demanding&quot; but I was really STRUCK of how arrogant Mr. Salarda was. His service was so unacceptable.&nbsp;Long story but I felt so bad to recieve such phone reception and treatment. If your hospital is a government agency then I will definitely report this incident to the Civil Service Commission. I really wish my concern be addressed or might wait for our futute 8888 hotline to bring this concern.&nbsp;I will be willing to reply to any quesstions you will ask me to further discuss this incident.</p>', '07/12/2016 06:58:55 pm', 'read', 'Done'),
