(1466, 'Roberto Rivera Jr.', '09813451000', 'clustersblue@gmail.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'info', 'Revised Statement of Account with Philhealth deduction', '<p>Ma&#39;am/Sir,</p><p>Good Day!</p><p>I&#39;m currently processing reimbursement claim in maxicare. &nbsp;Last June 2, 2016 my wife give birth in your hospital via normal delivery. &nbsp;After 3 days she was discharged, but our baby was re-admitted (extending for another day)&nbsp;for additional test. &nbsp;Eventually the baby was discharged the following day. &nbsp;When my wife was discharged we settled all the hospital&nbsp;charges including excess amounts not covered by our insurance. &nbsp;</p><p>However, in our baby&#39;s case since there was some lapses from our comapany to provide necessary documents to our insurance we end up paying all the charges. &nbsp;This is now the subject of my reimbursement claim in maxicare. &nbsp;After submitting all the needed document including the original copy of the hospital&nbsp;receipt they returned it to us and asking for a Revised Statement of Account with Philhealth deduction. &nbsp;</p><p>As per their advice, we need to coordinate this with you. &nbsp;As we don&#39;t know where to start, thus, I&#39;m sending this letter to ask for guidance on what needs to be done in order to get the need document. &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;I&#39;m asking for your assistance on how to go forward. &nbsp;Let me know to who I need to contact to.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks and Best Regards,</p><p>Roberto Rivera Jr.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '08/02/2016 02:19:13 pm', 'read', 'Done'),
