(1773, 'Gretcheen mae colina', '09237419117', 'gmpa_21@yahoo.com', 'Mandaue city', 'PH', 'Admin', 'Impolite staff at center for women', 'Hi good day! Im one of your customer and patient in cebu doc. This morning i went for a first time sonomammogram. While waiting for the doctor some staff were patiently responding to inquiry as to doctor was in or not. As the doctor arrive i went for a check had a nice conversation with the doctor which informed me to have the result consulted to my personal doctor that the lump found were cystic and nothing to worry due to lactation. As I went to waiting area, i thought the result wil be given to me just like pelvic ultrasound so i waited patiently. After couple of minutes i initiated to ask the staff in the desk as to how many minutes the result will be given. I was shocked that the other staff beside her responded in an impolite and harsh tone instead asking me twice what was the doctor told me. I was puzzled why she was answering my question with a question. To think a person wont be asking if they already know. I did not responded with a harsh tone to her as to avoid scandal in the room instead responded to her that the doctor told me to present the result to my personal doctor. I was really offended and dismayed with her manner and attitude toward me as if i was a kid and she does own the business and doesnt need customers. The guard says her name was maam tata she was sitting in front of computer from today shift 12/14/16 9am to 11am. When i went outside, my helper who happened to be with me during those time informed me that tata had an earlier harsh argument with another pregnant customer due to her harsh tone and manner of conversing while i was inside the bathroom. I was writing as a concerned customer. I dont think a customer who is acting and asking politely should be responded with a sarcastic manner like her. ', '12/14/2016 04:50:12 pm', 'read', 'Done'),
