(1798, 'Mafet Freeman', '407-779-3949', 'mcfreeman110404@netscape.net', 'Debary, Florida', 'US', 'Admin', 'Doctor\'s attitude', '<p>Good day!</p><p>I am writing this letter to express my biggest disappoint on how this certain Dr. Steven Seno of South General Hospital, Naga Cebu branch treated my family while my nephew was confined for dengue. I learned the whole story from my sister in law and my brother who happens to be the parents of the patient, &nbsp;Dave Cogal. It was disturbing enough for me that I had to make a long distance call to that branch hoping to talk to the administrator to address the issue right away. Unfortunately, it was only the supervisor I talked to but she was polite enough to tell me she will address the issue the following day to the administrator of the hospital. I will make myself very short and simple. First, this doctor discharged my nephew who had only 40,000 platelet count at that time and without his parent&#39;s knowledge and approval. I may not be in the medical field but I can gaurantee you, I know about malpractice. Secondly, because my brother and his wife did not agree to his suggestion which to have my nephew undergo a blood concentration procedure, he told them in an upset voice that they should be the one in medical field and walked out. He left my two sister in laws shocked and speechless with his attitude. This was also after my brother and his wife signed the waiver of refusal for the so called procedure. Mind you Doctor Seno, those two ladies you treated with no respect, they are college degrees.&nbsp;My main thing, he is not the one paying for all the expenses, why would he act like that and treat someone&nbsp;so low and most importanly he&nbsp;risked my nephew&#39;s life. &nbsp;&nbsp;I need someone to address this doctor&#39;s behavior and evaluate his practice regarding treating his patients and the patient&#39;s family as soon as possible because this kind of incident is not something that we can just take for granted. Imagine how many other patients and family&nbsp;he treated this way....Imagine those who are less privilege in life...Doctors and Nurses, they should be the patient&#39;s advocate regardless of the patient&#39;s status in life.</p>', '12/31/2016 11:20:06 am', 'read', 'Done'),
