(1844, 'Ramon Maria G. Santos', '09322589714', 'mon29166@gmail.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'Admin', 'Blood donation for my Mother with Stage 3 cancer.', 'To: Dr. Potenciano V. Larrazabal, M.D.<br />\nMedical Director<br />\nPresident and Chairman of the Board<br />\nCebu Doctors Hospital<br />\nOsmeña Blvd.<br />\n6000 Cebu City<br />\n<br />\nRequest for approval for blood extraction for my mother who has Stage 3 Cancer.<br />\n<br />\nDear Dr. Larrazabal,<br />\n      I am Ramon Maria G. Santos, son of Fe G. Santos who is a patient in your hospital. She is my mom, 86 years old and has Stage 3 Cancer. We were told by one of her primary doctors to prepare blood for her blood transfusion. My mom and I are both O+. I was declined by CDH blood bank because I tried (sniffed would be more accurate) a marijuana stick 35 years ago. I just sniffed it & threw it away. I have never been into prohibited drugs and/or dangerous substances. My mom can attest to that. <br />\n     My mom is dying and donating or giving my blood to her would probably give her the chance to live a little bit longer. I love my mom very much and I would give up my life for her. I am appealing to you Dr. Potenciano Larrazabal to let your hospital staff to screen my blood and hopefully extract my blood and give it to my mom by way of blood transfusion.<br />\n<br />\nI hope you will consider my request.<br />\n<br />\nRamon Maria G. Santos, son<br />\nFe G. Santos, patient, room 517, CDH<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n', '01/16/2017 12:20:39 am', 'read', 'Done'),
