(1852, 'Martin Burman', '09177507313', 'gunner_diver@hotmail.co.uk', 'Moalboal,Cebu', 'PH', 'Admin', 'Appointment with specialist.', '<p>Approx. 8 weeks ago I either trapped a nerve in my back or herniated a disc in my lumber region. I was in about 25-30% pain and unable to bend over. Three weeks ago I visited Dr. Pardis a chiropractor in the Ayala centre and after one treatment I am unable to stand or walk for more than 2 minutes. I spend 23 hours a day laying on my bed as any attempt to move causes me nerve pain from my sciatic nerve in my right side of my body down to my foot. In addition I have numbness of my toes in my right foot at all times. I am unsure if I need to see your neurologist or orthapedics doctors!!!!!</p><p>I await your reply.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kindest regards</p><p>Martin</p>', '01/20/2017 01:13:42 pm', 'unread', 'Pending'),
