(2032, 'guardian angel', '2555555', 'myshyangel00@gmail.com', 'cebu', 'PH', 'Admin', 'AGAINST OB RESIDENT/S and DOCTOR/S', '<p>Dear Sir/Ma&#39;am,&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I would like to write this letter against the OB doctors of CDUH. I don&#39;t know if this would count as a complaint. But the OB doctors just can&#39;t seem to stop themselves from admitting preterm pregnant mothers and delivering preterm babies even with the knowledge that there are no more warmers, incubators available for them. Some babies are forced to be placed on the cribs even if they could not properly keep themselves warm just to accommodate the new babies, or the newborn preterms are placed in the crib without the ideal heat source they need. There isn&#39;t even enough space to place a new warmer accordingly. Just because the OB doctors don&#39;t seem to understand the words FULL, NO WARMERS AVAILABLE, TRANSFER TO OTHER HOSPITALS, REFERRALS.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I don&#39;t know anymore if this institution is a PRIVATE or a PUBLIC hospital. If you could only look inside the present situation of the NICU, it is far from the ideal setting. Tiny babies inside a crib under 1-2 gooseneck lamps, it would scare you to think that should an accident happen, these babies might get burned by these lamps especially with their fragile skin.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Would it really be a big loss to them to transfer these patients to other hospitals and refer to other doctors especially if the hospital cannot provide the adequate care these patients are entitled to have? Shouldn&#39;t they be concerned with these tiny angels that will not be able to acquire the necessary attention and care that they absolutely need? They are dealing with LIVES, but it seems that their actions have no regard for the tiny, precious and fragile lives of these babies.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I am writing this, as I person whose heart is breaking at seeing this situation at hand. I also have a family, relatives, and friends, and we think highly of this institution. Should we have any health concerns, this institution is our go-to. But thinking of the present situation in the nursery, it makes us concerned for the care our pregnant relatives will be having should they conceive and for the care of the babies.</p><p>Will you please look into this matter before the situation gets out of hand.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thank You.</p>', '04/06/2017 05:01:21 pm', 'read', 'Done'),
(2033, 'Zsa Zsa balabat', '09778151198', 'zsazsa_balabat@yahoo.com', 'Sinai laguindingan misamis oriental', 'PH', 'info', 'Inquiry for estimated cost for nasal surgery', 'Good day!!! Pwede po bang makahingi ng estimated cost para sa nasal surgery... Yung patient po kasi namin sched for surgery dis coming april 17, 2017 here n cagayan de oro. Nagdalawang isip po kasi kami dahil yung explanation ng doctor dito eh walang kasiguraduhan.. Nais po naming kumuha ng second opinion at kung surgery ay mararapatin namin po na sa cebu doctors magpasurgery... Maraming salamat po. Plano naming pumunta sa cebu pag nakatanggap na kami ng estimated costs for the surgery..', '04/06/2017 09:07:38 pm', 'read', 'Done'),
