(2088, 'Lovella Nakayama', '2550157', 'lovella78@gmail.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'Admin', 'ER INCIDENT REPORT', '<p>DR. POTENCIANO V. LARRAZABAL, JR.</p><p>President and Chairman</p><p>Cebu Doctors&#39; University Hospital</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Through: Engr. Oscar A. Tuason</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Hospital Administrator</p><p>Dear Dr. Larrazabal,</p><p>I am currently living in Cebu City and a goverment employee. I would like to report an incident that happened yesterday in your hospital.&nbsp;</p><p>Around 9:45am yesterday&nbsp;I was at the hospital&#39;s emergency room with our grandfather. Few minutes later, PGI&#39;s I think were gathered across our cubicle as I think were preparing for a scenario at an ER about to film. THEY WERE VERY NOISY! Some directing what to do and laughing as if there were no patients around. I wondered in silence how could an expensive private hospital would allow such a thing! The noises were getting too loud and it was really getting out of hand. That&#39;s it!! I went out and gave them a statement but when I went back in they were still loud so I couldn&#39;t help but rant!&nbsp;<br />The head nurse and a resident Doctor apologized to us afterwards saying that they already told them to keep their voices down but still didn&#39;t listen, even asking for nurses on duty to be part of their filming.&nbsp;<br />I have high respect for people in the medical field and I truly admire them but what happened inside the ER today is very UNETHICAL and it shouldn&#39;t be allowed in any hospital.</p><p>I hope this will report will be acted upon promptly. Call the attention and give sanctions to those involved. &nbsp;I actually went to the administrators office to report this at around 11:30am but no one was inside the office.</p><p>Your official investigation report on the matter is highly appreciated.</p><p>Thank you.</p>', '04/28/2017 05:52:21 pm', 'read', 'Pending'),
