(2329, 'Georgia Padillo', '09173127560', 'georgia.padillo@marriott.com', 'Cebu City', 'PH', 'hr', 'Emergency Room Staffs Insufficient Service', '<p>Early today, my father&nbsp;was scheduled for a CT Scan in your hospital. He was diagnosed having a Intraparenchymal Hematoma (11cc) at the right Cerebellar Hemisphere. It is not a surprised to me that your ER ramp is not that patient-friendly since we have to travel few steps to arrive on your ER door. We are on hazzard mode down stairs and guards was just simply looking at us (trying to figure out if we need assistance or not) Hello! if a car is on hazzard and we&#39;re trying to get some stupid wheelchair of yours it&#39;s a CLUE that we need ASSISTANce. but this is not my main complain..it was very frustrating of the kind of service you&#39;ve given to my father. One nurse on duty&nbsp; between 9-10AM sa ER and the security guard there just instructed us to surrender 1 valid ID and get a wheelchair due to lack of manpower for olderly. i asked assistance if i can get 1 olderly to assist us, and both of them told me &quot;Ma&#39;am kuha lang sa ug wheelchair kay usa ra amua olderly on duty and wla lain makaassist&quot; Is that a proper way answering your guests concerns? is that the correct verbiage of the instituition? it is not my problem if your lacking a manpower like olderly what i need of is someone who can assist us&nbsp; on getting my father from the car to the ct&nbsp; scan section. I had a long discussion with Shecille Tulda (ER Manager as she claimed it) and the nurse involve of the incident. They told me that she will do the necessary actions to her staff. I agreed to that but this one should ring a bell to the owners and Board of Directors. If some of your patients don&#39;t take time to complain or doesnt have enough courage to speak but not me. This incident should ring a bell to your Heads. I want an action plan from your end. Thank you.</p>', '08/09/2017 11:47:13 am', 'read', 'Done'),
