(10, 'CDUH unveils newest Digital Radiography Facility', '2015-03-03', 'Cebu Daily News', '<p>Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University Hospital (CDUH) now offers the newest innovation in the radiography technology that rolls clarity, precision and ease of patients&rsquo; medical information storage in one. Last February 20, the hospital launched its Digital Radiography (DR) facility, the first installation of high-end digital X-ray technology in Cebu and in the country.</p><p>Cebuanos are privileged to be the first market in the country to experience the most advanced diagnostic system at a reasonable price. With the newest and direct DR facility manufactured by Samsung, X-ray procedures become faster and more reliable because soon as the patient undergoes the X-ray scanning, the resulting digital image directly appears from the radiographer&rsquo;s work station in the fastest turn-around time of three seconds. With the use of the machine&rsquo;s advanced S-Detector, a clear and vivid image of a patient&rsquo;s anatomical structure is displayed thus preventing misdiagnosis from occurring. The detector also lowers the radiation dose for radiographers and patients.</p><p>Dr. Troy Uy, general manager of the exclusive distributor of the facility in Cebu namely Marpont Enterprises and Bullseye Solutions said that the digitalized radiography allows easy exchange of a patient&rsquo;s medical records among doctors from any part of the island which makes patient record-keeping and tracking more convenient.</p><p>While Cebu is blazing the trail for digital radiography in the country, Uy said that the facility can be installed and made available in other islands in the country especially in the remote areas with the help of the Department of Health (DOH)</p>', 'upload/CDUH_unveils_newest_Digital_Radiography_Facility.jpg'),
(11, 'Women: A Homage', '2015-04-14', 'Rhodesa Cruzet', '<p>In line with the celebration of March being International Women&rsquo;s month, ArtPortal Cebu in cooperation with Banilad Town Centre present &ldquo;WOMEN: A HOMAGE&rdquo;, an art exhibit showcasing 14 women painters from different backgrounds and different artistic styles. Exhibiting artists are: Betsy Alterado, Karby Beloy, Bambi Beltran, Evangeline Caya, Rhodesa U. Cruzet, Juvy Harmelin, Golda King, Meriam King, Ann Lubanga, Stella Palomo Monte&ntilde;o, Gigi Ocampo, Celina Paredes, Fe Madrid Pepito and Lurline Rodriguez. The exhibit opened last March 27, 2015 at the 2nd level of Banilad Town Centre and runs until April 27, 2015.</p>', 'upload/women.JPG'),
(12, 'CDUH Medical Mission', '2015-04-27', 'Admin', '<p>Last April 18, 2015, Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University Hospital had their annual medical mission held at the Sacred Heart Parish Church at Escario St., Cebu City. There were more than 400 patients given free medical, pediatric, dental, optical and surgical services by the hospital during the medical mission.</p><p>The activity started at 9am and ended at 3 o&rsquo;clock in the afternoon. Check-ups for medical were given to 141 adults, pedia for 147, circumcision for 36, dental for 31 patients, and eye check-ups for 45 patients. Forty (40) patients were also given reading glasses, ECG test for 70, and laboratory test for CBS and BT for 150 patients.</p><p>There were four (4) barangay beneficiaries namely: Kamputhaw, Capitol, Kalunasan and some parts of Lahug. Medicines were distributed to all beneficiaries. Free snacks and drinks were also given to all patients while waiting for their turns.</p><p>The medical mission was supported by Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University Hospital (CDUH) and partners from different drug companies, the Community Outreach Services (COS) of Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University. Manpower services were provided by volunteer staff from CDUH and student volunteers from CDU.</p><p>Doctors, interns, optometrists, dentists, surgeons, nurses, pharmacy staff, social workers, HR and admin staff volunteered for the activity.</p><p>The activity was scheduled specifically in the month of April in relation to the 75th birthday of the Hospital&rsquo;s President, Dr. Potenciano V. Larrazabal, Jr.</p><p>This is one way of showing that Cebu Doctors&rsquo; University Hospital really cares by giving back to the community and sharing our resources with our less-fortunate members of the community.</p>\r\n\r\n<div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"gallery\">\r\n    <hr />\r\n    <h5>Photo Gallery</h5>\r\n    <br />\r\n	<div id=\"links\">\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../i