(19, 'CDUH: WE LEAD TO SERVE, THE MEDICAL MISSION PROGRAM', '2016-04-29', 'Admin', '<p>The parishioners of San Roque Parish Mambaling, Cebu benefited from the medical mission last April 16, 2016.\r\n<p>More than 600 patients were given Free Medical Check-up, Pediatric, Surgical for the Libre Tuli Service, Optical and Dental Check-up. Services such as medical consultations were given to 200 adults, Pedia for 157 patients, Libre Tuli for 107 patients. Sixty- six (66) were also given Free Reading Glasses, 100 for eye-checkups, ECG Test for 110 Patients, and 120 patients for CBS and BT. Free snacks and drinks were also distributed to the patients. </p>\r\n<p>Rev. Sarmago, the Parish Priest, expressed his gratefulness to Cebu Doctors’ University Hospital especially to Dr. Potenciano V. Larrazabal, Jr. who will celebrate his 76th Birthday, and to all the staff who volunteered, and for this wonderful opportunity they’d experienced.</p>\r\n<p> “We are so grateful for.. sa among pagdawat sa limpyu, limpyu nga pangihanglang medical para sa among mga parokyano nga makakalouy intawn kaayo,” Rev. Fr. Miguelito Sarmago exclaimed.</p>\r\n<p>The Medical Mission Program was supported by Cebu Doctors’ University Hospital Administrator and partners from different drug companies and the Community Outreach Services (COS) of Cebu Doctors’ University.</p>\r\n<p>Manpower services were provided by volunteer staff from CDUH and student volunteers from CDU. Doctors, interns, optometrists, dentists, surgeons, nurses, pharmacy staff, social workers and admin staff were the volunteers for the activity.</p>\r\n<p>It was another momentous day; yet serving thy community is one way for us to showing our love and care for the less fortunate members of the society. </p>\r\n<div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"gallery\">\r\n    <hr />\r\n    <h5>Photo Gallery</h5>\r\n    <br />\r\n	<div id=\"links\">\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../im