(39, 'TEAM REWARDS WINNER FOR THE MONTH OF APRIL 2017', '2017-06-07', 'Admin / HR', '<strong><p>TEAM REWARDS WINNER FOR THE MONTH OF APRIL 2017</p></strong>\r\n<p>\r\n    Last May 31, 2017, The Outstanding Team for the Month of April has been recognized.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Winners for the Non-Nursing Category:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 13</strong> composing <strong>PHARMACY Department</strong> ranked <strong>1st place</strong> as they got the average rate of 79.52%.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 7</strong> composing <strong>Business Unit 3</strong> ranked <strong>2nd place</strong> with the average rating of 77.26%.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 11</strong> composing <strong>Laboratory Group 1</strong> ranked <strong>3rd place</strong> with the average rating of 74.36%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Winners for the Nursing Category:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 16</strong> composing <strong>ER/ENDOSCOPY UNIT</strong> ranked <strong>1st place</strong> with the average rating of 75.61%.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 21</strong> composing <strong>DELIVERY ROOM/NURSERY</strong> ranked <strong>2nd place</strong> with the average rating of 72.09%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>HALL OF FAMER</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Team 5</strong> composing <strong>Business Office 2</strong> and <strong>Team 5</strong> composing <strong>Business Office 1</strong> qualifies for the Hall of Famers title as they reach the average rating required. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications to become Hall of Famer:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A team who has won five (5) wins as First Placer will be considered a HALL OF FAMER in a period of one year; or</li>\r\n    <li>A team who has won a total of ten (10) wins in either 1st, 2nd or 3rd place will be considered as HALL OF FAMER in a period of one year; or</li>\r\n    <li>A team who has won First Place in three consecutive months will be considered as HALL OF FAMER in a period of one year.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The awards were given by Dr. Potenciano V. Larrazabal, Jr., President and Chairman of the Board and Engr. Oscar A. Tuason, Hospital Administrator. It was also attended by the Admin Circle Heads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><font size=\"5\">Congratulations to all the winners!</font></strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div role=\"tabpanel\" class=\"tab-pane\" id=\"gallery\">\r\n    <hr />\r\n    <h5>Photo Gallery</h5>\r\n    <br />\r\n    <div id=\"links\">\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/1.JPG\" data-gallery title=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\" alt=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/1.JPG\" class=\"img-responsive thumbnail\"/>\r\n                </a>                \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/2.JPG\" data-gallery title=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\" alt=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/2.JPG\" class=\"img-responsive thumbnail\"/>\r\n                </a>                \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/3.JPG\" data-gallery title=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\" alt=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/3.JPG\" class=\"img-responsive thumbnail\"/>\r\n                </a>                \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/4.JPG\" data-gallery title=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\" alt=\"THE MOST OUTSTADING TEAM\">\r\n                    <img src=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/4.JPG\" class=\"img-responsive thumbnail\"/>\r\n                </a>                \r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <div class=\"col-sm-3\">\r\n                <a href=\"../../images/gallery/april2017/5.JPG\" data-ga