(14, '2019-12-23', 'thumbnail/petctscanthumbnail.jpg', 'petctscan/petctscanheader.jpg', 'cebudoc-launches-a-stronger-fight-against-cancer', 'cebu doc, cebu doc group, cebu doctors university hospital, fight againts cancer, PET CT scan, CT Scan', 'CebuDoc launches a stronger fight against Cancer', 'Cebu Doctors University Hospital, a proud member of CebuDoc Group, kicks off another healthcare breakthrough in Visayas and Mindanao - Positron Emission Tomography and Computed Tomography (PET-CT) Scan is now made available in Cebu.', '    <section class=\"mbr-section article content1 cid-content-body\" id=\"content1-mt\">\r\n    \r\n\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\r\n            <div class=\"mbr-text col-12 col-md-8 mbr-fonts-style display-7\">\r\n                <p>\r\n                    Cebu Doctors University Hospital, a proud member of CebuDoc Group, kicks off another healthcare breakthrough in Visayas and Mindanao - Positron Emission Tomography and Computed Tomography (PET-CT) Scan is now made available in Cebu.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    This newest diagnostic facility in CebuDoc  has the capability to image a wide range of patients over a wide range of applications with superior image quality and high throughput performance.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    PET-CT Scan is a combination of two types of imaging-Positron Emission Tomography and Computed Tomography, which is combined to create special views. It is useful in revealing or evaluating several conditions, including cancers, heart diseases, brain disorders such as Alzheimer\'s disease, depression, epilepsy, head trauma, Parkinson\'s disease, and problems with the central nervous system.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                     “It is a highly sensitive imaging technique used in oncology, cardiology, neurology, and infectious and inflammatory diseases\" said Mrs. Yvonne Pahaganas, Head of CebuDoc Center for Nuclear Medicine.\r\n                </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<section class=\"mbr-section article content1 cid-content-body\" id=\"content1-mt\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"mbr-text col-12 col-md-8 mbr-fonts-style display-7\">\r\n                <h2 class=\"pb-3 mbr-fonts-style display-5\">Most Advanced Technology For Cancer Detection</h2>\r\n                <p>\r\n                    According to the World Health Organization (WH0), Cancer is the second leading cause of death globally and is responsible for an estimated 9.6 million death in 2018. About 1 in 6 deaths is due to cancer.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    The new PET-CT Scan is used to accurately detect cancer and show how far it has spread. It may also help in the diagnosis of certain heart and neurological disorders. PET Scan and CT Scan are done simultaneously where CT is used for the localization of abnormalities seen in PET.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    The PET Scan shows areas with increased metabolic activity and help doctors’ evaluate how well organs and tissues are functioning, while CT Scan shows detailed anatomical locations. These are important in the early detection of cancer to determine the kind of treatment the patient should receive.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    \"With the advantage of both anatomic and physiologic imaging in PET-CT, it can give the most accurate disease assessment to help clinicians in deciding for the optimal care of their patients\" said Dr. Henry Cañizares, Nuclear Medicine Physician.\r\n                </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>\r\n\r\n\r\n<section class=\"mbr-section article content1 cid-content-body\" id=\"content1-mt\">\r\n    <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\r\n            \r\n            <div class=\"mbr-text col-12 col-md-8 mbr-fonts-style display-7\">\r\n                <h2 class=\"pb-3 mbr-fonts-style display-5\">Quality Patient Care</h2>\r\n                <p>\r\n                    PET-CT scan is described to be a safe, painless, and non-invasive procedure. There are certain preparations to be followed before scanning but with the team of experts that CebuDoc has, optimal care is assured.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    \"The procedures will be done by our well-trained Radiation Safety Officers, PET-CT Technologists and duly certified Nuclear Medicine Physicians so our patients can be guaranteed that in CebuDoc, our procedures are properly indicated and executed,\" said Dr. Potenciano \"Yong\" Larrazabal, III, CebuDoc Group\'s President and Chairman.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    Known to be the country\'s Most Outstanding Hospital for Level 3 Private, CebuDoc assured the patients with excellent care that will provide their needs and comfort effectively without compromising the efficiency of the procedure.<br><br>\r\n\r\n                    To know more about PET-CT scan, It is now ready to serve patients from Monday to Friday, from 7AM to 4PM, and conveniently located at the Basement of Cebu Doctors University Hospital. You may contact 255-5555 local 767 for inquiries and reservations.\r\n                </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</section>', '   <div class=\"container\">\r\n        <div><!-- Filter --><!-- Gallery --><div class=\"mbr-gallery-row\"><div class=\"mbr-gallery-layout-default\"><div><div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"0\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/001-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"1\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/002-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"2\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/003-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"3\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/004-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"4\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/005-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"5\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/006-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"6\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/007-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"><span class=\"icon-focus\"></span></div></div><div class=\"mbr-gallery-item mbr-gallery-item--p1\" data-video-url=\"false\" data-tags=\"Animated\"><div href=\"#lb-gallery1-0\" data-slide-to=\"7\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img src=\"../../../assets/images/pressrelease/petctscan/008-2000x1328-800x531.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"